The paper deals with turnstile streaming algorithms and linear sketching, which are both topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of space complexity and communication complexity, as well as computational complexity (cs.CC) in terms of the hardness of linear sketching. The paper also discusses applications to data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of the limitations of linear sketching for certain problems.
